---
title: Blackened Fish Tacos with Caramelized Pineapple and Red Cabbage Slaw
description: Think you know pineapple? Think again. You haven’t truly experienced it until it’s been warmed through and caramelized to bring out all of its juicy sweetness. And when you toss it into a taco with some gently spiced pieces of catfish and a crispy slaw, everything you think is true about the fruit is suddenly flipped on its head as you venture into savory dinnertime territory.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/blackened-fish-tacos-f8fdce33.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/blackened-fish-tacos-900bae91.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/blackened-fish-tacos-59565476c6243b5b400e2002
time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Fusion
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 710 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Drain @pineapple{4%oz}. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges. Pat @catfish{11%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}. Sprinkle with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle @Cajun spice blend{1%tbsp} onto fillets, then gently rub into fish to moisten.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat (use an #ovenproof pan{} if you have one). Add pineapple and cook, tossing, until browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of vegetable oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add catfish and cook until browned on surface, about ~{2%minutes} per side. Transfer to oven and let bake until opaque and flaky, ~{8-14%minutes}.

> TIP: Transfer fish to a lightly oiled baking sheet first if your pan isn't ovenproof.

Peel @carrots{1}. Using a #vegetable peeler{}, shave carrot lengthwise into long ribbons, rotating as necessary. Discard carrot core once it becomes too thin to shave. Add carrot, @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, juice from lime half, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a large pinch of salt and pepper to a #medium bowl{}. Toss until thoroughly combined.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in a damp paper towel and microwave on high until warm, ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: Alternatively, wrap tortillas in foil and place in oven to warm, about 3 minutes.

Stir pineapple into slaw. Spread tortillas with @sour cream{2%tbsp}. Break up catfish into bite-sized pieces and divide between tortillas. Top each with slaw. Tear @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves from stems and scatter over top. Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.